Javascript cookies
----------------

cookies are tiny pieces of data a website stores on your computer to remember things like your login, 
shopping cart details, in the form of name-value pairs like:  username = John Doe

CREATE:

 document.cookie = "name = value; expires="date"; path=/";

READ:
 let x = document.cookie;  // return all cookies in one string

CHANGE:

same way as you create it & The old cookie is overwritten.

DELETE:
To delete a cookie, you don't need to specify a value. 
document.cookie="username=;"

